This application uses pre-trained model weights and source code from the
following third-party projects. Their respective licenses apply to their
respective components.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1. DermLIP Model Weights & Derm1M Dataset
   License : CC BY-NC-ND 4.0
             https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0/
   Source  : https://huggingface.co/redlessone/DermLIP_PanDerm-base-w-PubMed-256
   Paper   : Yan, S. et al. (2025). "Derm1M: A Million-Scale Vision-Language
             Dataset Aligned with Clinical Ontology Knowledge for Dermatology."
             arXiv:2503.14911. https://arxiv.org/abs/2503.14911

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2. PanDerm Vision Encoder
   License : See https://github.com/SiyuanYan1/PanDerm
   Paper   : Yan, S. et al. (2025). "A multimodal vision foundation model for
             clinical dermatology." Nature Medicine, pp. 1–12.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3. OpenCLIP (Derm1M custom fork)
   License : MIT License
             https://github.com/mlfoundations/open_clip/blob/main/LICENSE
   Source  : https://github.com/SiyuanYan1/Derm1M (src/open_clip/)

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
4. PubMedBERT Text Encoder
   Source  : https://huggingface.co/NeuML/pubmedbert-base-embeddings
   License : MIT License

